  "texts": [
    "The string mentions are normalised.",
    "Afterwards, the candidates are searched using three different techniques: (1) by acronym, if the mention is classified as an acronym, (2) by label, relying on the set of surface forms which were generated, and (3) by context, using the TF-IDF metric.",
    "24 Finally, a disambiguation graph is constructed to extract the optimal candidate.",
    "This step is equivalent to the disambiguation approach of AGDISTIS [181] based on HITS 25 and PageRank.",
    "26 MAG was recently extended to support 40 languages, including low-resourced languages such as Ukrainian, Greek, Hungarian, Croatian, Portuguese, Japanese and Korean [119]."
  ],
